verbs.description: intitle (third-person singular simple present intitles, present participle intitling, simple past and past participle intitled)

entries.meaning: (archaic or nonstandard) Alternative form of entitle
examples: Jones answered all his questions with much civility, though he never remembered to have seen the petty-fogger before; and though he concluded, from the outward appearance and behaviour of the man, that he usurped a freedom with his betters, to which he was by no means intitled.
